intro: Hutchinsia rotundifolia subsp. cenisia, commonly known as the Cape York hutchinsia, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It is characterized by its small, round leaves and clusters of white or pale yellow flowers. The species belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and tea trees. It typically grows in moist, shaded environments such as rainforests or swampy areas. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for ecological and taxonomic studies.
